          :marked
            Prime Minister Scott Morrison’s position on the alliance is very
            much in the tradition of his Liberal predecessors: [“A strong
            America – centrally engaged in the affairs of our region – is
            critical to Australia’s national interests.”][1]
            Morrison has also said that [Asia is entering a period of 
            heightened competition between the US and China][2].
            The Turnbull-Morrison Government was disappointed by the Trump
            Administration’s decision to withdraw from the Trans Pacific
            Partnership trade deal, and has worked to revive it without the US.

            [1]: https://www.pm.gov.au/media/keynote-address-asia-briefing-live-beliefs-guide-us
